Title: Stability and BPS branes
Authors: Michael R. Douglas, Bartomeu Fiol and Christian R\"omelsberger
Comments: harvmac, 18 pp
Report-no: RUNHETC-2000-05
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Algebraic Geometry
\\
  We define the concept of Pi-stability, a generalization of mu-stability of
vector bundles, and argue that it characterizes N=1 supersymmetric brane
configurations and BPS states in very general string theory compactifications
with N=2 supersymmetry in four dimensions.
